---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const title = "Top 10 UNSC Leader Powers Ranked - Halo Wars 2";
const description = "A subjective ranking of the top 10 active UNSC leader powers in Halo Wars 2. From Johnson's Bunker to Ghost in the Machine, discover which powers dominate the battlefield.";
const category = "Reviews";
const publishedDate = "February 2, 2026";
const dateIso = "2026-02-02";
const tags = ["Halo Wars 2"];
const ogImage = "/content/blog/reviews-placeholder.svg";
---

<BlogPostLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  category={category}
  publishedDate={publishedDate}
  dateIso={dateIso}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  tags={tags}
  youtubeId="GyySuLrif5Y"
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    This is a subjective ranking of the top 10 <strong>active</strong> leader powers for the UNSC in Halo Wars 2, based on casual team play. Only offensive leader powers that can be dropped to cause damage or battlefield changes - no passive abilities like Johnson's line of sight upgrade or Anders' sentinel spawns from Kodiaks.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">#10: Johnson's Bunker</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Not technically offensive since it can't damage units when dropped, but incredibly useful:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Originally consumed population at launch (3 pop, then 4 with shield upgrade) - was useless back then</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Synergy with Pavium</strong>: Pavium in a bunker is a beloved strategy</li>
    <li>Great for protecting Snipers and Marines</li>
    <li>Mastodon is similar but consumes pop and is mobile</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#9: Grizzly Battalion (Forge)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">The Grizzlies vs Scorpions debate exists (Isabel's shielded Scorpions are strong), but Grizzly Battalion has unique advantages:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Grizzlies consume more population than Scorpions</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Three veteran Grizzlies</strong> with Pelican protection on drop</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Gunship Glitch</strong>: Sometimes the gunship stays permanently (unkillable, can't be targeted)</li>
    <li>Best counter is Omega Team - hijack all three Grizzlies</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#8: Sentinel Network (Anders)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">An excellent utility power that provides vision and distraction:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Great for distraction (draws aggro)</li>
    <li>Provides excellent line of sight across the entire map</li>
    <li>On maps like Vault, Badlands, or Sentry: See opponent movements, base control, unit positions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#7: Cryo + Seismic Blast Combo (Serina)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Combined because together they're much better than individually:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Critical</strong>: Never drop Seismic without Cryo first</li>
    <li>When upgraded: Multiple shots of each with single use</li>
    <li>Simply amazing when executed properly</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#6: Inferno (Kinsano)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Used to be better in older patches, but still effective in the right situations:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Was insane on ground units, now not as effective</li>
    <li>Maybe worth dropping on massed infantry</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Best use</strong>: On bases (especially UNSC bases)</li>
    <li>Take down shield first, then Inferno</li>
    <li>Destroys individual buildings (Gens, War Councils, units being trained)</li>
    <li>Can interrupt Scarab production</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#5: Scatter Bomb (Forge)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">The community calls it "Lag Bomb" for good reason:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Hard to escape once bombs start falling</li>
    <li>Difficult to dodge</li>
    <li>Quick wind-up time compared to other powers</li>
    <li>Works great on air, ground, and sometimes bases</li>
    <li>All around great power</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#4: Enduring Salvo (Jerome)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Falling garbage from the sky that's incredibly powerful:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Can lose whole army to this power</li>
    <li>Quick regeneration/cooldown time</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Best non-ultimate drop</strong> in the UNSC roster</li>
    <li>Superior to EMP Mac Blast and regular Mac Blast</li>
    <li>Jerome's leader wheel is generally great</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#3: Omega Team (Jerome)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">One of the best unit drops in the game:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Four Spartans total</strong>: Commander Jerome + Mantis + three Omega Team Spartans</li>
    <li>Requires 30 pop (10 each Spartan)</li>
    <li>All Spartans inspire units like Jerome does</li>
    <li>Great for commanding Mastodons or hijacking enemy vehicles</li>
    <li>Perfect counter to Grizzly Battalion</li>
    <li>One of the favorite leader powers overall</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#2: Combat Salvage</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Insane when used correctly - not technically "offensive" but affects offensive units:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Best with Vultures</strong>: Combat Salvage Vultures</li>
    <li>Meta leans into mass Vultures/cringe air</li>
    <li>Full pop Vultures twice in short succession is devastating</li>
    <li>Works with Scorpions, Mass Hornets, any vehicles</li>
    <li>Mantis and Colossus combo also works great</li>
    <li>Hard to face leaders with Combat Salvage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">#1: Ghost in the Machine (Isabel)</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">The <strong>complete game changer</strong> when used correctly:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Many games turned from losing to winning with a good drop</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Best targets</strong>: Vultures, Scarabs, Condors</li>
    <li>Reduces opponent's attacking units</li>
    <li>Aggro opponent's units onto their own temporarily controlled units</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Advanced Trick</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Hold position the controlled units on the other side of the map</li>
    <li>When opponent regains control, hold position command sometimes persists</li>
    <li>If they're not paying attention, they must manually remove it</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Ultimate troll</strong>: Steal units, destroy their base, tell units to hold position elsewhere</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Summary</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Here's the complete ranking of the top 10 UNSC leader powers:</p>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Ghost in the Machine (Isabel)</strong> - Complete game changer</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Combat Salvage</strong> - Devastating with Vultures</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Omega Team (Jerome)</strong> - Four inspiring Spartans</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Enduring Salvo (Jerome)</strong> - Best non-ultimate drop</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Scatter Bomb (Forge)</strong> - The "Lag Bomb"</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Inferno (Kinsano)</strong> - Base destroyer</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Cryo + Seismic Combo (Serina)</strong> - Deadly when combined</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Sentinel Network (Anders)</strong> - Vision and distraction</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grizzly Battalion (Forge)</strong> - Veteran tank drop</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Johnson's Bunker</strong> - Defensive powerhouse</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="mb-4 mt-6">
    Each of these powers can turn the tide of battle when used effectively. Master their timing and combos to dominate your opponents on the battlefield!
  </p>

</BlogPostLayout>
